      "message": "Clarifying a bit more....\n\nr_dir_file(storaged, proc)\nr_dir_file(storaged, domain)\n\nThe two rules above allow you to read files, directories, and symlinks associated with /proc/PID entries. In addition, it allows you to read files, directories, and symlinks associated with files in /proc (outside of /proc/PID) which have the \"proc\" label.\n\nwhereas....\n\nallow storaged proc:dir r_dir_perms;\nr_dir_file(storaged, domain)\n\nallows you to read files, directories, and symlinks associated with /proc/PID entries. But does NOT allow you to read files or symlinks associated with /proc files outside of /proc/pid.\n\nFor example, the file /proc/devices would be readable with the former, but not the latter.",
